Notes.Text:
This update for openldap2 fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2022-29155: Fixed SQL injection in back-sql (bsc#1199240).

Vulnerabilities.Description: In OpenLDAP 2.x before 2.5.12 and 2.6.x before 2.6.2, a SQL injection vulnerability exists in the experimental back-sql backend to slapd, via a SQL statement within an LDAP query. This can occur during an LDAP search operation when the search filter is processed, due to a lack of proper escaping.
